title: For Sale:  1945 Lithgow (Australian) Enfield No.1 Mk.3 Improved with walnut cheek piece, scope mount (Bachelder Master Gunmakers) Simmons 22 Mag scope, Huber Concepts trigger, ammo, dies.
postcontent: Don't pay what those other jokers want for a decent enfield. Get yourself a nice one with a scope for a decent price from me. I've taken good care of her. Shot my first deer with this rifle. Still has a really good looking bore with strong rifling. Bore is on the darker side as they go but it's not eroded or pitted. Lightly sticking a .312 hornady SST in the muzzle it stops immediately. It's still a pretty new bore as they go, just wasn't cleaned regularly by the previous owner. The Huber Concepts trigger I put in it along with a light stoning of the sear and striker have made it a really light pull. Haven't measured it but I've pulled a lot of triggers. I'd call it well under 2 1/2lbs. I refinished this wood and put the cheekpiece on with a nicer scope and had given it to my father as a gift bit the light pull surprised him in a bad way so I decided to get him a nicer CZ Mauser finally. It's a really nice enfield though. Pretty minimally altered too. I wouldn't call it a collector but people want a lot even for a really bubba'd one now. Considering that I have dies, brass, bullets, scope and mount, the trigger, cheek rest, it's worth what I want for it and it's hard to find a nicer hinting rifle for the price. Ammo I loaded is on the light side but 150gr SST still hits like lightning. Come right with my asking price and don't bother haggling or I won't respond. Don't have time to shorten my life span stressing over clowns.
